Testimony 3 from Portsman claims that "And when Jim came to deliver some evidence to me, I was down at Criminal Affairs." This means that when Buddy Faith (the victim) arrived, Portsman was not present, and therefore did not see Buddy Faith.

However, Evidence 2 (Victim's Revolver) is the murder weapon, and the case facts and logical deductions show the killer had to have been present when Buddy Faith was there, in order to take his gun and kill him. The murderer stole Jim's revolver (Buddy Faith's gun) and killed him with it. Portsman claiming he was absent ("down at Criminal Affairs") at the time contradicts the fact that he had to be present to obtain the gun and commit the murder.

